# Common Object Patterns

When working on Object Discovery or Object Guides, these patterns appear frequently
across many product domains. Use them as a starting point, not a prescriptive list.

## Universal Objects (Present in Most Products)

| Object | Purpose | Common Attributes |
|--------|---------|-------------------|
| USER / ACCOUNT | Identity and authentication | name, email, avatar, role, status |
| NOTIFICATION | System-to-user communication | title, body, type, read/unread, timestamp |
| COMMENT | User-to-user communication | body, author, timestamp, parent reference |
| TAG / LABEL | Categorization and filtering | name, color, description |
| FILE / ATTACHMENT | Media and document storage | name, type, size, URL, upload date |
| SEARCH RESULT | Discovery and navigation | title, snippet, relevance score, source |

## Domain-Specific Patterns

### Education / LMS
USER, COURSE, LESSON, ASSIGNMENT, SUBMISSION, GRADE, ENROLLMENT, CERTIFICATE

### E-Commerce
USER, PRODUCT, ORDER, CART, PAYMENT, SHIPPING, REVIEW, CATEGORY, WISHLIST

### Project Management
USER, PROJECT, TASK, MILESTONE, SPRINT, BOARD, BACKLOG, LABEL, COMMENT

### Content / CMS
USER, ARTICLE, PAGE, MEDIA, CATEGORY, TAG, COMMENT, REVISION, TEMPLATE

### Healthcare
PATIENT, PROVIDER, APPOINTMENT, RECORD, PRESCRIPTION, INSURANCE, FACILITY

### SaaS / B2B
ORGANIZATION, TEAM, USER, WORKSPACE, INTEGRATION, BILLING, PLAN, INVITE

## Object Relationship Patterns

### Containment (1:many, owned)
```
ORGANIZATION → TEAM → MEMBER
PROJECT → MILESTONE → TASK
COURSE → MODULE → LESSON
```

### Reference (many:many, independent)
```
USER ←→ ROLE (via ASSIGNMENT)
TASK ←→ TAG (via TAGGING)
STUDENT ←→ COURSE (via ENROLLMENT)
```

### Lifecycle States (common patterns)
```
Draft → Active → Archived → Deleted
Pending → Approved → Rejected
Open → In Progress → Done → Closed
```

## Object Guide Template Checklist

When creating an Object Guide, ensure you cover:
- [ ] Object title (user-friendly name)
- [ ] Also known as (synonyms, legacy names)
- [ ] Purpose statement (2-3 sentences)
- [ ] Core user (who interacts with it most)
- [ ] 3-5 concrete instances
- [ ] Attributes table (name, type, required, views)
- [ ] CTA list (with roles and context)
- [ ] Relationships (parents, children, references)
- [ ] Lifecycle states
- [ ] Edge cases and business rules
- [ ] Open questions
